id: pm-klqo
title: "CLI silently corrupts --tags '[\"a\",\"b\"]' JSON-array input (agent-unfriendly)"
description: "Dogfood 2026-05-17: `pm create --tags '[\"a\",\"b\"]'` saves tags as `[\"[\\\"a\\\"\", \"\\\"b\\\"]\"]` with no warning. Critical agent-blocker because MCP server normalizes JSON arrays to CSV but the CLI parser does not, so agents copying examples from tool schemas end up with broken data.\n\nFix proposal: in src/cli/commands/create.ts parseTags() and equivalent in update.ts, if the raw string trims to a JSON array (starts with [) try JSON.parse and treat the array as the tag list. Apply same to other CSV-style fields (skills, blockedBy) wherever the CLI accepts them.\n\nAcceptance: tests cover CSV input, JSON array input, mixed/spaced input; existing CSV behavior unchanged."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[8]: agent-ux,bug,cli,create,parsing,pm-cli,tags,update
created_at: "2026-05-17T05:49:42.738Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T08:15:43.959Z"
deadline: "2026-05-20T05:49:42.738Z"
author: claude-code-agent
resolution: "Verified fixed: parseTags() in src/core/item/parse.ts:27-66 already accepts JSON-array input via coerceJsonTagArray() (commit 46a225b). Dogfood test in /tmp confirms --tags '[\"a\",\"b\"]' produces tags=[a,b] correctly."
expected_result: "Expected result: closure includes explicit resolution metadata and verifiable delivery evidence."
actual_result: "Actual result: Verified fixed: parseTags() in src/core/item/parse.ts:27-66 already accepts JSON-array input via coerceJsonTagArray() (commit 46a225b). Dogfood test in /tmp confirms --tags '[\"a\",\"b\"]' produces tags=[a,b] correctly."
close_reason: "Verified fixed: parseTags() in src/core/item/parse.ts:27-66 already accepts JSON-array input via coerceJsonTagArray() (commit 46a225b). Dogfood test in /tmp confirms --tags '[\"a\",\"b\"]' produces tags=[a,b] correctly."
